																EXPERIMENT 4
																------------



1. Update the price of a particular product.
mysql> UPDATE PRODUCT SET PRICE =30 WHERE PID =1;  //MENTION THE PRODUCT NAME LIKE 'PEN'
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.08 sec)
Rows matched: 1  Changed: 1  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT *FROM PRODUCT;
+-----+---------+-------+
| PID | PNAME   | PRICE |
+-----+---------+-------+
|   1 | PEN     |    30 |
|   2 | BOOK    |    75 |
|   3 | UMBERLA |   200 |
|   4 | BOX     |   100 |
|   5 | OPIUM   |  4000 |
+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)


2.Change the name of city ‘CLT’ to ‘kozhikode’ in the customer table.

mysql> UPDATE CUSTOMER SET CITY = 'KOZHIKODE' WHERE CITY ='CLT';
Query OK, 2 rows affected (0.04 sec)
Rows matched: 2  Changed: 2  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT *FROM CUSTOMER;
+----+--------+---------+-----------+-------+
| ID | NAME   | ADDRESS | CITY      | PH_NO |
+----+--------+---------+-----------+-------+
|  1 | SUGU   | KDY     | KDY       |  6268 |
|  2 | SUNI   | TSY     | EKM       |  NULL |
|  3 | MANU   | TSY     | TVM       |  NULL |
|  4 | ARNOLD | KDY     | KOZHIKODE |  9562 |
|  5 | ANU    | KDY     | KOZHIKODE |  9563 |
|  6 | ANN    | KDY     | EKM       |  9563 |
+----+--------+---------+-----------+-------+
6 rows in set (0.00 sec)


3.Update all prices with 2% of its original price.


mysql> UPDATE PRODUCT SET PRICE=PRICE*1.02;
Query OK, 5 rows affected (0.04 sec)
Rows matched: 5  Changed: 5  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT *FROM PRODUCT;
+-----+---------+-------+
| PID | PNAME   | PRICE |
+-----+---------+-------+
|   1 | PEN     |    31 |
|   2 | BOOK    |    77 |
|   3 | UMBERLA |   204 |
|   4 | BOX     |   102 |
|   5 | OPIUM   |  4080 |
+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)


4.Change the address, city, phone number of a particular customer.

mysql> UPDATE CUSTOMER SET ADDRESS='JDK',CITY='USA',PH_NO=1111 WHERE ID=1;
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.04 sec)
Rows matched: 1  Changed: 1  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT *FROM CUSTOMER;
+----+--------+---------+-----------+-------+
| ID | NAME   | ADDRESS | CITY      | PH_NO |
+----+--------+---------+-----------+-------+
|  1 | SUGU   | JDK     | USA       |  1111 |
|  2 | SUNI   | TSY     | EKM       |  NULL |
|  3 | MANU   | TSY     | TVM       |  NULL |
|  4 | ARNOLD | KDY     | KOZHIKODE |  9562 |
|  5 | ANU    | KDY     | KOZHIKODE |  9563 |
|  6 | ANN    | KDY     | EKM       |  9563 |
+----+--------+---------+-----------+-------+
6 rows in set (0.00 sec)



5.Change the quantity of a purchased product of inv_id ‘101’


mysql> UPDATE INVOICE_ITEM SET QUANTITY=20 WHERE INV_ID=101;  //PRODUCT ID NEEDED IN CONDITION
Query OK, 2 rows affected (0.04 sec)
Rows matched: 2  Changed: 2  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT *FROM INVOICE_ITEM;
+--------+------+----------+
| INV_ID | PID  | QUANTITY |
+--------+------+----------+
|    101 |    1 |       20 |
|    101 |    3 |       20 |
|    102 |    4 |        2 |
|    102 |    5 |        1 |
|    103 |    5 |        1 |
|    104 |    2 |        4 |
|    105 |    2 |        6 |
|    106 |    3 |        6 |
|    107 |    4 |       10 |
|    108 |    1 |       20 |
+--------+------+----------+
10 rows in set (0.00 sec)






